Abuja Furniture Product (AFP) the furniture and furnishing arm of Julius Berger Nigeria Plc, has won the ‘Recognition for Corinthian Partnership Award’ of the Nigerian Institute of Architects, Lagos State Chapter. AFP also won the ‘Company with Most Popular Product Award’ at the Lagos Architects Forum 13.0, which was held in Lagos. The Lagos Architects Forum described the Julius Berger AFP as unique and supportive of the architectural profession even as the Chapter Chairman, Arch. David Majekodunmi described AFP’s products on display at the accompanying exhibition as, “Unique, superb and uniquely lovely.” Representative of the governor of Lagos State and Special Adviser to the state Chief Executive on Infrastructure and Engineering Services, Engr Mrs Aramide Adeyoye who also won an award of Excellence, lauded the Nigeria Institute of Architects for “A well organised Forum and Exhibition.”